In the firs semester, seminars introduce theories widely used in the study of languages and cultures and their possible range of applications. In the second semester, seminars are dedicated to the discussion of the students' MA thesis ideas and the possible theoretical and methodological approaches to the thesis. Students make presentations on the different stages of their developing theses, provide feedback to each other and engage in an interdisciplinary discussion with their peers.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the seminar is to help the students of the different specialities of the European languages and cultures MA curriculum to develop their understanding of theories relevant for the study of European languages and cultures, to develop their MA thesis, provide many-sided feedback to the developing work and to develop the students' presentation and communication skills in English.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students develop theoretical knowledge and skills necessary for conducting research in the area of foreign languages and cultures as well as the skill of academic presentation and communication in English and the foreign language of their speciality.
